dismissalText.commentary: Jonathan Trott c Jones b Mooney 69 (105b 6x4 0x6 158m) SR: 65.71

dismissalComment.html: the first forcing shot Trott has timed in ages, and it's landed right in the lap of the only man out on the midwicket boundary! The ball was full, the shot was on, and Trott found the middle of the bat - but the fielder didn't have to move. Another wicket, and Ireland will be loving this.

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c & b Stirling 59 (65b 6x4 1x6 73m) SR: 90.76

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! What a celebration! Stirling tossed another one up and Morgan turned the bat too early as he looked to nudge to leg, the ball taking the leading edge and flying back to the left of Trott. It didn't look as though Stirling would get close to it, but he shuffled quickly to his left and leapt, full stretch, to pluck it out of the air. That wicket meant a lot, and Stirling boots the ball out into the deep in celebration with a big smile

cracking ball, and that's the breakthrough! It's been coming for Mooney, who has plugged away on a good length, and that one did just enough. Kieswetter committed, the ball seamed, and O'Brien did the rest. A quick pause to check the no-ball, but all clear

headshotImage.caption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: and that's that. Play and a miss to end the game which means England win a scrappy match quite comfortably

commentPostTextItems.html: England win by 11 runs Not the most memorable match with rain ruining a good occasion. England's bright young things flunked with the bat but were pretty good with the ball. A game that looked tight half-way became easy and unsatisfactory as rain had its way. Eoin Morgan is named man of the match and gets to collect the trophy. Must feel a little awkward surely? Mind you I don't think Morgan ever feels anything. Jonathan Trott, by the way, top-scored in the game. Anyway, more of that and other things in Andrew Miller's report. That's all from us, thanks for the emails.

commentTextItems.html: Dockrell ran down the wicket and outside leg. Dernbach was full and outside off so the batsman had to leave it
shot! The little man goes big! Full toss thrashed down the ground for four
very quick from Dernbach. Too quick for Dockrell
Cusack manages a single in the end. He horribly mistimed this back to the bowler but with Dockrell haring up the other end Dernbach aimed a shy - and missed - the overthrow collected the single

commentPreTextItems.html: Righty 19 runs to win from 6 balls. Dernbach to bowl it.

commentTextItems.html: clubbed with plenty of inelegance down the ground but only for one
touch of spin unnerves Cusack as he comes down the  ground. Ends up skewing a drive out to Finn at deep point

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson c Bopara b Patel 13 (14b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 92.85

commentTextItems.html: smart bowling with a touch of air and spin gets Patel reward. Wilson had to try and find the boundary but ended up with an outside edge that looped towards Bopara who clung on
grim mis-hit toe-ended down the ground. Top work from Patel
Wilson skips down and slugs across the line but is through the shot too early and it hits his pad
flash and a miss outside off this time! Excellent work from the bowler

commentPreTextItems.html: Samit Patel is the man to bowl it. 12 deliveries left in the game.

commentTextItems.html: good start from Patel - full and straight - bunted back to the bowler
slower ball ends a decent over. Worked carefully to short third man. England are favourites but one big over will change that swiftly

headshotImage.caption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: slower ball is flipped to deep square where Finn runs in sharply to prevent two
"no!" screams Bopara as he bowls. Rightly so - it was shoved down the leg side
big swing at fresh air as Cusack fails to spot a slower ball
slower ball is dabbed to point for a single

commentPreTextItems.html: Looks like Patel is warming up.

commentTextItems.html: top shot! Third man comes into the ring and Wilson squeezed it past him for four

commentPreTextItems.html: England have a meeting with the umpires to work out who can bowl. Bopara and Dernbach have one each left.

commentTextItems.html: good delivery around off stump worked to point

dismissalText.commentary: John Mooney c Stokes b Dernbach 15 (8b 1x4 1x6 11m) SR: 187.5

commentTextItems.html: ah Mooney almost got enough here. Smashed it down the ground and Stokes did well on the boundary edge to hold on above his head

commentPostTextItems.html: We definitely have a match too now that 20 overs are up. Ireland need 32 from 18

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Kieswetter c NJ O'Brien b Mooney 14 (26b 1x4 1x6 32m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: cracking ball, and that's the breakthrough! It's been coming for Mooney, who has plugged away on a good length, and that one did just enough. Kieswetter committed, the ball seamed, and O'Brien did the rest. A quick pause to check the no-ball, but all clear

headshotImage.caption: Boyd Rankin player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Boyd Rankin player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: James Taylor c Wilson b Rankin 1 (8b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 12.5

dismissalComment.html: all over for Taylor! His much-anticipated first international innings ends with a top-edge pull that looped to midwicket. Good bouncer from Rankin and sound reward for a good morning's work

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c & b Stirling 59 (65b 6x4 1x6 73m) SR: 90.76

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! What a celebration! Stirling tossed another one up and Morgan turned the bat too early as he looked to nudge to leg, the ball taking the leading edge and flying back to the left of Trott. It didn't look as though Stirling would get close to it, but he shuffled quickly to his left and leapt, full stretch, to pluck it out of the air. That wicket meant a lot, and Stirling boots the ball out into the deep in celebration with a big smile

headshotImage.caption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Bopara c NJ O'Brien b Jones 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: gone! What was Bopara trying to do? Jones landed another ball on a good length, this one nibbling away off the wicket, and Bopara just stood at the crease and thrust his bat out at it, the thin edge pouched safely by O'Brien. There's an audible sigh from Sahil as Ravi departs for another low score, another chance gone begging

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ben Stokes c & b Stirling 3 (10b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 30

dismissalComment.html: there's another one! Stokes had been under pressure from the start of his innings. He drove hard, and perhaps a little too early, at this one to send the ball straight back to the bowler, who made no mistake. Stirling has his second.

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Samit Patel c KJ O'Brien b Jones 13 (12b 2x4 0x6 12m) SR: 108.33

dismissalComment.html: Patel perishes in the pursuit of quick runs! He tried to go over long-off but could only get as far as Kevin O'Brien, and England have been pegged back by another timely wicket.

headshotImage.caption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jonathan Trott c Jones b Mooney 69 (105b 6x4 0x6 158m) SR: 65.71

dismissalComment.html: the first forcing shot Trott has timed in ages, and it's landed right in the lap of the only man out on the midwicket boundary! The ball was full, the shot was on, and Trott found the middle of the bat - but the fielder didn't have to move. Another wicket, and Ireland will be loving this.

headshotImage.caption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Scott Borthwick c Stirling b Mooney 15 (9b 1x4 1x6 10m) SR: 166.66

dismissalComment.html: there's another one! Borthwick perishes in the cause, looking to go over the midwicket boundary but getting only as far as Stirling's save pair of hands

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce c Kieswetter b Finn 10 (22b 2x4 0x6 28m) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: Finn gets his reward! Second wicket for him as he holds this on off stump again and Joyce outside edges to the keeper. With every wicket Trott's innings looks more valuable

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling c Bopara b Finn 6 (3b 0x4 1x6 6m) SR: 200

dismissalComment.html: oh dear. What a waste. Having played a couple of nice strokes Stirling slogs across the line and gets an edge that loops to Bopara at cover

headshotImage.caption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Scott Borthwick, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield run out (Borthwick/Kieswetter) 15 (37b 3x4 0x6 44m) SR: 40.54

dismissalComment.html: happy to throw it up once more, it's worked to leg but Porterfield wanted a single that wasn't quite there and took an age to turn back. Very gently he ended up being run out as Borthwick scampered round and flicked back to Kieswetter before the Ireland captain could return

headshotImage.caption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Niall O'Brien c Finn b Dernbach 13 (24b 1x4 0x6 33m) SR: 54.16

dismissalComment.html: gone! Niall O'Brien picks out Finn at deep square. Slower bouncer and Niall O'Brien couldn't keep his pull shot down

headshotImage.caption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin O'Brien b Dernbach 26 (15b 2x4 2x6 18m) SR: 173.33

dismissalComment.html: that's probably the match! Brilliant bowling! After all those slower ones Dernbach has rocked in a yorker at almost 90mph. O'Brien can't get his bat down in time!

headshotImage.longCaption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nigel Jones player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nigel Jones b Bopara 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: gone! Bopara gets his man! Back of the hand slower ball and Jones was through the shot a good hour early. Had time to watch it clip the top of his middle stump

headshotImage.caption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Samit Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson c Bopara b Patel 13 (14b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 92.85

dismissalComment.html: smart bowling with a touch of air and spin gets Patel reward. Wilson had to try and find the boundary but ended up with an outside edge that looped towards Bopara who clung on
